        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/11634565-while-the-light-lasts">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2513756842" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer226959202551972409">This is a nice collection of early Agatha Christie stories. Two of the stories feature Poirot – “Christmas Adventure,” and “The Mystery of the Baghdad Chest,” which also involves Hastings.<br/><br/>Some of these stories are fairly rare and not all are mysteries – there is one sentimental love story, for example. One of the stories, “The Edge,” is particularly interesting for fans of Christie, as it was written in 1926, the year she disappeared and involves Claire Halliwell, a hard working parish worker. C</span>
  <span id="freeText226959202551972409" style="display:none">This is a nice collection of early Agatha Christie stories. Two of the stories feature Poirot – “Christmas Adventure,” and “The Mystery of the Baghdad Chest,” which also involves Hastings.<br /><br />Some of these stories are fairly rare and not all are mysteries – there is one sentimental love story, for example. One of the stories, “The Edge,” is particularly interesting for fans of Christie, as it was written in 1926, the year she disappeared and involves Claire Halliwell, a hard working parish worker. Claire has long been in love with Sir Gerald, but he has married the glamorous city girl, Vivien. The story revolves around infidelity and jealousy, and it gives some insight into her tumultuous feelings in that most difficult year. Overall, a good collection with some very good, rare, stories. <br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="226959202551972409" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


