    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3001561852" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3001561852" />
    <a title="fleurette" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4692637-fleurette"><img alt="fleurette" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1357165343p2/4692637.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3001561852?book_show_action=true">Oct 07, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="fleurette" class="user" itemprop="url" name="fleurette" href="/user/show/4692637-fleurette">fleurette</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4692637-fleurette?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4692637-fleurette?shelf=short-stories">short-stories</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3001561852" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer822109644939015080"><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1570648109i/28269654._SX540_.jpg' width='400' height='320' alt='While the Light Lasts' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>I am not a big fan of stories in general, I also had the opportunity to read Agatha Christie&apos;s stories before and I was not particularly delighted with them. I definitely prefer her novels. The stories I found a bit boring. That&apos;s why I&apos;m surprised that I rather enjoyed this collection of stories, despite the low ratings of other reviewers. Maybe I am just in the mood for something like that.<br/><br/>The stories are really short. And there are a lot of them in this collection. They are also very differen</span>
  <span id="freeText822109644939015080" style="display:none"><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1570648109i/28269654._SX540_.jpg" width="400" height="320" alt="While the Light Lasts" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>I am not a big fan of stories in general, I also had the opportunity to read Agatha Christie's stories before and I was not particularly delighted with them. I definitely prefer her novels. The stories I found a bit boring. That's why I'm surprised that I rather enjoyed this collection of stories, despite the low ratings of other reviewers. Maybe I am just in the mood for something like that.<br><br>The stories are really short. And there are a lot of them in this collection. They are also very different from each other. From well-known criminal stories (including ones with Hercule Poirot) through romance to short sketches from the borderland of genres. I am not entirely sure if that is a good thing. The whole collection seems a bit random. Although maybe thanks to this it is also more interesting, and the stories are so short that even if one is not in your taste then you get the next one.<br><br>Two stories, both about Hercule Poirot, were published in other books in a slightly changed version. And so I had read them before. And although I don't remember all the details, when I read them now they weren’t as interesting to me. Was this a big problem? No, not necessarily. But if I didn't know them, they would probably be the most interesting stories in this collection.<br><br>The whole volume takes its title from the last story in the collection, which in my opinion is not the best or any particularly interesting. Nor is it a strictly crime story, typical for Agatha Christie's work (though not necessarily for this collection). I don't know where this decision came from. It is not even the longest story in this collection. And I am not particularly delighted with it.<br><br>But generally, the stories are nice. You read them very quickly, even if sometimes you can see that these are very early works of the author.</span>
  <a data-text-id="822109644939015080" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


