        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3783751018" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10352019576303366821">There are nine short stories in this volume.Poirot appears in two stories,The Mystery of the Baghdad Chest (about a crime of breathtaking audacity) and The Adventure of the Christmas Pudding (which I found rather lukewarm).<br/><br/>The Lonely God and Within a Wall are not works of detective fiction but are romantic stories,from the earliest period of Christie&apos;s career.<br/><br/>Christie,rather surprisingly, wrote one of the stories,Manx Gold, for a fee of just 60 pounds,though she was an established author.It was </span>
  <span id="freeText10352019576303366821" style="display:none">There are nine short stories in this volume.Poirot appears in two stories,The Mystery of the Baghdad Chest (about a crime of breathtaking audacity) and The Adventure of the Christmas Pudding (which I found rather lukewarm).<br /><br />The Lonely God and Within a Wall are not works of detective fiction but are romantic stories,from the earliest period of Christie's career.<br /><br />Christie,rather surprisingly, wrote one of the stories,Manx Gold, for a fee of just 60 pounds,though she was an established author.It was about a treasure hunt.<br /><br />The House of Dreams and While the Light Lasts have an element of the supernatural.Jealous lovers and the eternal love triangle are the subject of some of the stories in this volume.<br /><br />(Christie had herself endured trouble in her first marriage and her husband Archie Christie married another woman).<br /><br />Not all the stories are of the highest quality,but there are some very good ones among them,which compensate for the weaker ones.<br /><br />3.5 stars,rounded up.</span>
