<div id="review_2449542273" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2449542273" />
    <a title="Riju Ganguly" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2736147-riju-ganguly"><img alt="Riju Ganguly" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1524633338p2/2736147.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2449542273?book_show_action=true">Jul 08, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Riju Ganguly" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Riju Ganguly" href="/user/show/2736147-riju-ganguly">Riju Ganguly</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2449542273" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12132705450723439766">These stories depict a side of Dame Christie&apos;s writings which often get overlooked by those who know her only as the creator of Hercule Poirot mysteries. Of course, the unique literary gaze that throws light upon unspoken features of human psyche and illuminates her mysteries are all present here. The collection also contains some purpose-written mysteries as well as very British love stories. But for me, it&apos;s special because of the haunting story: &apos;The House of Dreams&apos;. Despite being one of her</span>
  <span id="freeText12132705450723439766" style="display:none">These stories depict a side of Dame Christie's writings which often get overlooked by those who know her only as the creator of Hercule Poirot mysteries. Of course, the unique literary gaze that throws light upon unspoken features of human psyche and illuminates her mysteries are all present here. The collection also contains some purpose-written mysteries as well as very British love stories. But for me, it's special because of the haunting story: 'The House of Dreams'. Despite being one of her earliest stories, this one is vintage Christie.<br />If you can get hold of this collection, do read it.<br />Recommended.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12132705450723439766" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


