<div id="review_4117976328" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4117976328" />
    <a title="Gail Sacharski" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25211167-gail-sacharski"><img alt="Gail Sacharski" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1383261785p2/25211167.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4117976328?book_show_action=true">Jul 16, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gail Sacharski" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gail Sacharski" href="/user/show/25211167-gail-sacharski">Gail Sacharski</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780006510185" href="/book/show/1124560.While_the_Light_Lasts_and_Other_Stories">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4117976328" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2431296887829617489">This collection of Christie short stories were all previously published elsewhere--magazines, other collections. This collection was published after her death. Some of the stories are slightly different versions perhaps with different characters, altered details, plot devices used in other stories. This collection has forewards and/or afterwords which give a bit of history &amp; background for each &amp; add to the interest &amp; enjoyment. At first, I was tempted to skip over those I&apos;d read before, but the</span>
  <span id="freeText2431296887829617489" style="display:none">This collection of Christie short stories were all previously published elsewhere--magazines, other collections. This collection was published after her death. Some of the stories are slightly different versions perhaps with different characters, altered details, plot devices used in other stories. This collection has forewards and/or afterwords which give a bit of history &amp; background for each &amp; add to the interest &amp; enjoyment. At first, I was tempted to skip over those I'd read before, but then re-read them to see what, if any, changes were there. I enjoyed it &amp; the book completes my Christie collection.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2431296887829617489" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


